g new ways to hinder access for an exponentially growing minority population. She warns that a premeditated strategy of restrictive laws and deceptive practices has taken root and is eroding the very basis of American democracy—the right to vote!  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aElectionsxCorrupt practiceszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aElectionsxCorrupt practiceszUnited States. 0aSuffragezUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSuffragezUnited States. 0aSuffrage-United States. 0aVoter registrationxCorrupt practiceszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aVoter registrationxCorrupt practiceszUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Campaigns & Elections.2bisacsh  aactivism.  aadvocacy.  aafrican american.  aamerican citizens.  aconstitutional rights.  ademocracy.  ademocratic party.  adiscrimination.  afelon disenfranchisement.  agerrymandering.  agrandfather clauses.  aid requirements.  aliteracy test.  aminority voters.  apoll tax.  aracial justice.  arepublican party.  arigged elections.  ashelby ruling.  avoter fraud.  avoter initmidation.  avoter restrictions.  avoting rights act.  avoting rights.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472340uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479883479.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479883479423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479883479/original  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  